      "children":  [{
          "text": "The Secret of Tension ‚Äì From Unstable to Stable",
          "id": "harmony-5-1"
        }]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "For the C major scale, 1 is the most stable tone. In the G7 chord, 7 is only a half-step away from 1, and 4 is only a half-step away from 3. It‚Äôs like being about to reach stability but getting stuck. Let‚Äôs try moving from G7 to C."
