    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Doesn‚Äôt that feel satisfying now? This shift from 'uncomfortable' to 'comfortable' is called 'resolution' in music theory."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Eating sweet cake all the time makes us tired of it. If we add a bit of bitter matcha in between, making it less comfortable, then return to the sweet cake, it feels good again. This process of 'conflict => resolution' is the source of human satisfaction. Always being comfortable can actually become uncomfortable. You‚Äôve probably experienced how boring it is when every day is a holiday, yet how exciting Friday feels during school time."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The two uncomfortable notes in G7 move by half-step to the stable C chord, turning 'uncomfortable' into 'comfortable.'"
        }
      ]
    },
