        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "These sonic characteristics can guide your chord connections. The G7‚ÄìC progression (V‚ÄìI) we mentioned is very common because of the half-step resolution, but you can also deliberately use I‚ÄìV for a fresh sound. In modern music, you can connect any diatonic chords freely‚Äîeverything serves the ear."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "By now, do you have a basic grasp of music theory? If you have questions, feel free to email me via the address on my homepage or ask the AI robot at the top of the page (*^‚ñΩ^*)."
        }
